00', 'type': '010combined'}, {'absolute_url': '/opinion/7316187/united-states-v-menendez/', 'attorney': 'Peter Koski, Amanda Rose Vaughn, Joseph Patrick Cooney, Monique Tara Abrishami, U.S. Department of Justice, Washington, DC, for Plaintiff., Abbe David Lowell, Chadbourne" & Parke LLP, Washington, DC,\' Jenny R. Kramer, Chadbourne & Parke LLP, New York, NY, for Defendant Robert Menen-dez. -, Anne Marie Lyons, Maria A. Dominguez, Not A Member of N.J. Bar, Matthew I. Menchel, Kobre & Kim, LLP,’Miami, FL, Matthew I. Menchel, Kobre & Kim LLP, New York, NY, Kirk Ogrosky, Arnold & Porter LLP, Murad S. Hussain, Arnold & Porter LLP, Washington, DC, for Defendant Salomon Melgen.', 'author_id': None, 'caseName': 'United States v. Menendez', 'citation': ['137 F. Supp. 3d 688', '2015 WL 5915749'], 'citeCount': 1, 'cites': None, 'cluster_id': 7316187, 'court': 'District Court, D. New Jersey', 'court_citation_string': 'D.N.J.', 'court_exact': 'njd', 'court_id': 'njd', 'court_jurisdiction': None, 'dateArgued': None, 'dateFiled': '2015-08-08T00:00:00-07:00', 'dateReargued': None, 'dateReargumentDenied': None, 'date_created': '2022-07-24T21:36:54.976578-07:00', 'docketNumber': 'Cr. No. 15-155', 'docket_id': 64304670, 'download_url': None, 'id': 7234094, 'joined_by_ids': None, 'judge': 'Walls', 'lexisCite': '', 'local_path': None, 'neutralCite': '', 'ordering_key': None, 'panel_ids': None, 'per_curiam': False, 'scdb_id': '', 'sibling_ids': [7234094], 'snippet': "Judge\nDefendant Robert Menendez moves to dismiss Count Twenty-Two of the indictment in this criminal case, which charges him with falsifying, concealing, or covering up material facts in financial statements he filed with the Secretary of the <mark>United</mark> <mark>States</mark> Senate,, on multiple grounds. After oral argument on September 17, 2015, thq Court denies this motion. '\nPROCEDURAL AND FACTUAL BACKGROUND\nOn April 1, 2015, Defendants Robert Menendez, who has represented New Jersey in the United States Senate", 'status': 'Precedential', 'suitNature': '', 'timestamp': '2025-07-08T14:20:43.207319-07:00', 'type': '020lead'}, {'absolute_url': '/opinion/10749842/united-states-v-frances-eddings/', 'attorney': '', 'author_id': None, 'caseName': 'United States v. Frances Eddings', 'citation': None, 'citeCount': 0, 'cites': [47932, 118098, 340752, 491468, 702500, 1036870, 1266240, 1439120, 2400107, 2653744, 2669619, 2764885, 3134116, 4279548, 4692447, 7236042, 7246450, 8413726, 8414419, 8414421, 9352237, 9431127, 9487823, 9908434, 10464739], 'cluster_id': 10749842, 'court': 'Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit', 'court_citation_string': '3rd Cir.', 'court_exact': 'ca3', 'court_id': 'ca3', 'court_jurisdiction': 'F', 'dateArgued': '2025-09-18T00:00:00-07:00', 'dateFiled': '2025-12-09T00:00:00-08:00', 'dateReargued': None, 'dateReargumentDenied': None, 'date_created': '2025-12-09T10:00:20.477556-08:00', 'docketNumber': '23-3017', 'docket_id': 71368615, 'download_url': 'https://www2.ca3.uscourts.gov/opinarch/233017p.pdf', 'id': 11216427, 'joined_by_ids': None, 'judge': '', 'lexisCite': '', 'local_path': 'pdf/2025/12/09/united_states_v._frances_eddings.pdf', 'neutralCite': '', 'ordering_key': None, 'panel_ids': None, 'per_curiam': False, 'scdb_id': '', 'sibling_ids': [11216427], 'snippet': '                                      PRECEDENTIAL\n\n      <mark>UNITED</mark> <mark>STATES</mark> COURT OF APPEALS\n           FOR THE THIRD CIRCUIT\n                ____________\n\n                    No. 23-3017\n                   _____________\n\n          UNITED STATES OF AMERICA\n\n                          <mark>v.</mark>\n\n    FRANCES M. EDDINGS, a/k/a Fran Eddings,\n\n                                               Appellant\n\n          ________________\n\n     Appeal from the United States District Court\n        for the Eastern District of', 'status': 'Precedential', 'suitNature': '', 'timestamp': '2025-12-09T10:00:42.829675-08:00', 'type': '010combined'}, {'absolute_url': '/opinion/4534006/united-states-v-zenaido-renteria-jr/', 'attorney': '\n  Susan M. Lin, Esq. [Argued], Kairys Rudovsky Messing & Feinberg, 718 Arch Street, Suite 501 South, Philadelphia, PA 19106, Attorney for Appellant\n , \n  Louis D. Lappen, United States Attorney, Bernadette A. McKeon, Esq. [Argued], Andrew J. Schell, Esq., Robert A. Zauzmer, Esq., Office of the United States Attorney, 615 Chestnut Street, Suite 1250, Philadelphia, PA 19106, Attorneys for Appellee\n ', 'author_id': None, 'caseName': 'United States v. Zenaido Renteria, Jr.', 'citation': ['903 F.3d 326'], 'citeCount': 5, 'cites': [2667, 104316, 105684, 118216, 407824, 623849, 772798, 774999, 776532, 783949, 797379, 1024452, 2311338], 'cluster_id': 4534006, 'court': 'Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit', 'court_citation_string': '3rd Cir.', 'court_exact': 'ca3', 'court_id': 'ca3', 'court_jurisdiction': None, 'dateArgued': None, 'dateFiled': '2018-09-11T00:00:00-07:00', 'dateReargued': None, 'dateReargumentDenied': None, 'date_created': '2018-09-11T10:00:20.649448-07:00', 'docketNumber': '17-2079', 'docket_id': 7842868, 'download_url': 'http://www2.ca3.uscourts.gov/opinarch/172079p.pdf', 'id': 4311259, 'joined_by_ids': None, 'judge': 'Greenaway, Rendell, Fuentes', 'lexisCite': '', 'local_path': 'pdf/2018/09/11/united_states_v._zenaido_renteria_jr..pdf', 'neutralCite': '', 'ordering_key': None, 'panel_ids': None, 'per_curiam': False, 'scdb_id': '', 'sibling_ids': [4311259], 'snippet': 'conspiracy cases, we decline to do so.\n \n\n  Venue is a concept that stems from the Constitution itself, which "twice safeguards the defendant\'s venue right."\n  \n   6\n  \n  First, Article III mandates that "[t]he Trial of all Crimes ... shall be held in the <mark>State</mark> where the said Crimes shall have been committed."\n  \n   7\n  \n  Second, the Sixth Amendment reiterates, "[i]n all criminal prosecutions, the accused shall enjoy the right to a speedy and public trial, by an impartial jury of the State and dis