helman, American Civil Liberties Union of the District of Columbia, Washington, DC, Esha Bhandari, pro hac vice, Rachel Goodman, pro hac vice, New York, NY, for Plaintiffs., John Russell Tyler, Serena Maya Schulz Orloff, Stephen J. Buckingham, U.S. Department of Justice, Washington, DC, for Defendant.', 'author_id': None, 'caseName': 'Sandvig v. Sessions', 'citation': ['315 F. Supp. 3d 1'], 'citeCount': 2, 'cites': None, 'cluster_id': 7330563, 'court': 'Court of Appeals for the D.C. Circuit', 'court_citation_string': 'D.C. Cir.', 'court_exact': 'cadc', 'court_id': 'cadc', 'court_jurisdiction': None, 'dateArgued': None, 'dateFiled': '2018-03-30T00:00:00-07:00', 'dateReargued': None, 'dateReargumentDenied': None, 'date_created': '2022-07-24T22:37:55.768562-07:00', 'docketNumber': 'Civil Action No. 16–1368 (JDB)', 'docket_id': 64319047, 'download_url': None, 'id': 7248480, 'joined_by_ids': None, 'judge': 'Bates', 'lexisCite': '', 'local_path': None, 'neutralCite': '', 'ordering_key': None, 'panel_ids': None, 'per_curiam': False, 'scdb_id': '', 'sibling_ids': [7248480], 'snippet': '\nJOHN D. BATES, <mark>United</mark> <mark>States</mark> District Judge\nIt\'s a dangerous business, reading the fine print. Nearly every website we visit features Terms of Service ("ToS"), those *8endless lists of dos and don\'ts conjured up by lawyers to govern our conduct in cyberspace. They normally remain a perpetual click away at the bottom of every web page, or quickly scrolled past as we check the box stating that we agree to them. But to knowingly violate some of those terms, the Department of Justice tells us, could', 'status': 'Precedential', 'suitNature': '', 'timestamp': '2025-10-23T04:28:07.128290-07:00', 'type': '020lead'}, {'absolute_url': '/opinion/4482792/sandvig-v-sessions/', 'attorney': '', 'author_id': 201, 'caseName': 'Sandvig v. Sessions', 'citation': None, 'citeCount': 0, 'cites': [1741, 2144, 70831, 74535, 97699, 101341, 102662, 103950, 106761, 107045, 107701, 108592,